  "prompt": "Is six hours of sleep enough for a 10-year-old?",
  "response": "For a 10-year-old, six hours of sleep is generally not enough. According to the guidelines from the American Academy of Sleep Medicine, children aged 6-12 years typically need 9-12 hours of sleep per night for optimal health and development. \n\nGetting too little sleep can affect a child's mood, attention, behavior, and physical health. If a child is consistently getting less sleep than recommended, it may be helpful to assess their bedtime routine and sleep environment or consult with a healthcare provider for further guidance.",
